-- Peruvian Stocks: Pomalca, Relapasa, Rio Alto, Southern
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-03-20T21:19:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-20/peruvian-stocks-panoro-relapasa-rio-alto-southern.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of the close of trade.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 0.6 percent to 22,935.70. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  dropped 0.6 percent to 2,875.97.  Refineria la Pampilla SA  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Repsol
YPF SA known as Relapasa, slumped 4.6 percent to 1.04 soles
after crude fell the most in three months in  New York  and the
company said a ruling limiting sulfur levels in diesel will curb
earnings, said Jose Luis Bustamante, head of trading at Cartisa
SAB.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, declined 1.6 percent to $1.27.  Southern Copper Corp. (PCU\C)  (SCCO PE), Peruâ€™s biggest copper
producer, dropped 3.8 percent to $31.10 after copper fell the
most in two weeks in New York.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold miner, slid
2.3 percent to $4.30 after gold dropped in New York.  Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POM\C)  (POMALCC1 PE), a sugar
producer, fell 3.4 percent to 56 centimos after sugar declined
in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
